videos.description: Daxter Miles forces a turnover and then lays it in on the other end for the Mountaineers.
videos.headline: WVU gets early steal and score from Miles

videos.description: Sagaba Konate elevates for a two-handed block to prevent a Baylor basket to hold WVU's lead.
videos.headline: Konate rejects Baylor shot with two-handed block

videos.description: Sagaba Konate blocks a Terry Maston layup to keep West Virginia in the lead.
videos.headline: Kontae continues to dominate at the rim

videos.description: The Bears turn the ball over but Jevon Carter's shot is rejected by Jo Lual-Acuil Jr. on the other end.
videos.headline: Baylor answers with a block on Carter

videos.description: Nuni Omot works around the defense to make back-to-back jumpers, cutting West Virginia's lead in the second half.
videos.headline: Baylor closes gap with Omot's back-to-back jumpers

videos.description: Sagaba Konate shuts down the Bears with nine blocks in West Virginia's 71-60 win in Waco.
